question: 鮮魚
sourceMnemonic:
<kanji>Fresh</kanji> <kanji>fish</kanji> is <vocabulary>fresh fish</vocabulary> (and the best fish, nom nom nom).

This is a fairly specialized word that you’d mostly see at a market. To describe fresh fish more generally, you can just say <ja>新鮮な魚</ja>.
sourceReadingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word, which usually means on'yomi readings from the kanji. If you know the readings of your kanji you'll know how to read this as well.
